[{"body": "The Indonesian government's latest auction of sharia securities, or state sukuk, received IDR 17.47 trillion in incoming bids, with a total awarded amount of IDR 8 trillion from 7 series of state sukuk. This brings the total awarded amount from 21 state sukuk auctions since the beginning of 2024 to IDR 187.62 trillion, according to data from IDNFinancials.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51235/sukuk-auction-reported-incoming-bids-idr", "sub_sector": ["banks"], "tags": ["Sharia Economy", "Bonds", "Debt", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-10-23T11:56:16", "title": "Indonesian Government Raises IDR 8 Trillion from Latest Sharia Securities Auction"}, {"body": "PT Adiwarna Anugerah Abadi Tbk, a fire protection system service company, is set to raise up to IDR 80.25 billion through an initial public offering (IPO) of 750 million shares, priced between IDR 100 and IDR 107 per share. The IPO, led by PT MNC Sekuritas, will take place from October 24 to November 6, 2024, with listing scheduled for November 8, 2024.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "sector": "industrials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51234/adiwarna-anugerah-abadi-issue-ipo", "sub_sector": ["industrial-services"], "tags": ["IPO", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-10-23T10:51:25", "title": "PT Adiwarna Anugerah Abadi to Raise IDR 80.25 Billion Through Initial Public Offering of 750 Million Shares."}, {"body": "PT Jaya Agra Wattie Tbk has secured a loan of IDR 1.25 trillion from its shareholder, PT Sarana Agro Investama, which is expected to reduce interest expenses by 34-100%. This loan, combined with previous facilities, brings the total shareholder loan from PT Sarana Agro Investama to IDR 2.25 trillion, which will be used to facilitate business activities.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 1, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51233/jawa-secured-loan-worth-idr", "sub_sector": ["Food & Beverage"], "tags": ["Debt", "Interest Rates", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["JAWA.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-10-23T10:38:11", "title": "PT Jaya Agra Wattie secures IDR 1.25 trillion loan from affiliate PT Sarana Agro Investama to reduce interest expenses."}, {"body": "PT Medco Energi Internasional Tbk has repurchased senior bonds maturing in 2026 and 2027, with a total value of up to USD 100 million, reducing the company's obligations. As of June 2024, Medco reported total liabilities of USD 5.31 billion and total assets of USD 7.50 billion, with the buyback expected to improve its financial position.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51232/medc-set-buyback-senior-bonds", "sub_sector": ["Oil, Gas & Coal"], "tags": ["Debt", "Buyback", "Bonds", "Financial Ratios", "Balance Sheets", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["MEDC.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-10-23T10:32:41", "title": "Medco Energi Internasional repurchases senior bonds worth up to USD 200 million to reduce company obligations."}, {"body": "The Financial Services Authority (OJK) has revoked the business license of PT Investree Radika Jaya, a fintech company, due to its co-founder and CEO Adrian Asharyanto Gunadi's failure to meet evaluation standards and alleged fleeing of the country. Investree's financial report showed a total equity of IDR 48.81 billion and a default rate of 16.44%, significantly higher than the industry average, leading to the OJK's sanctions and asset inspections.", "dimensio