Consumer Services"], "tags": ["Dividends", "IDX", "IDX Composite", "Market Trends", "Earnings Report", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["CNMA.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-10-22T15:33:09", "title": "Cinema XXI's Managing Company to Distribute IDR 48.16 Billion Interim Dividend to Shareholders."}, {"body": "PT Hexa Prima Nusantara has acquired 99.99% of PT Digital Futura Global from PT Investasi Gemilang Maju, gaining indirect control over PT Lini Imaji Kreasi Ekosistem Tbk, with a total acquisition value of IDR 24.9 billion. The takeover aims to create business diversification and synergy between business ecosystems within the Hexa Group, with the transfer of shares taking effect yesterday.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51224/hexa-prima-controller-futr-dgf", "sub_sector": ["Media & Entertainment"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["FUTR.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-10-22T15:13:33", "title": "PT Hexa Prima Nusantara acquires 99.99% of PT Digital Futura Global, gaining indirect control over PT Lini Imaji Kreasi Ekosistem TBK."}, {"body": "Angela Tanoesoedibjo, the new Co-CEO of MNC Group, will lead the operation of MNC Media and iNews Media Group, leveraging her experience to drive innovation and excellence in the rapidly growing media industry. As Co-CEO, Tanoesoedibjo aims to improve media offerings and provide better services to the audience in Indonesia, building on her previous contributions to the tourism and creative economy industry during her tenure as Vice Minister from 2019 to 2024.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 2, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51219/term-angle-tanoesoedibjo-takes-position-co-ceo-mnc", "sub_sector": ["media-entertainment"], "tags": ["Executive Changes", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-10-22T11:18:12", "title": "Angela Tanoesoedibjo becomes Co-CEO of MNC Group after serving as Vice Minister of Tourism and Creative Economy."}, {"body": "Multiple investors, including PT BCA Sekuritas and individual investors, increased their stakes in PT Estika Tata Tiara TBK, a livestock company, by purchasing a total of 130.94 million shares. Meanwhile, several other investors, including PT MNC Sekuritas and UOB Kay Hian Ltd., reduced their stakes in various companies, releasing a total of 896.88 million shares, with transactions facilitated by PT MNC Sekuritas and other securities firms.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51218/estika-tata-tiara-beef-investors-raise-stake-company", "sub_sector": ["Food & Beverage"], "tags": ["Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "IDX", "Earnings Report", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["BEEF.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-10-22T11:12:14", "title": "Multiple investors increase stakes in PT Estika Tata Tiara TBK, a livestock company, through various share purchases and sales."}, {"body": "PT Newport Marine Services Tbk, an oil and gas industry vessel operator, will offer 1 billion shares through an initial public offering (IPO) on the Indonesia Stock Exchange, priced between IDR 100-120 per share, equivalent to 28.57% of its fully paid capital. The IPO is scheduled for October 21-25, 2024, with a public offering on November 4-6, 2024, and listing on November 8, 2024, with PT BRI Danareksa Sekuritas as the managing underwriter.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 1, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51217/newport-marine-services-releases-shares-ipo", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["IPO", "IDX", "IDX Composite", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-10-22T11:01:07", "title": "PT Newport Marine Services to Offer 1 Billion Shares in Initial Public Offering on Indonesia Stock Exchange"}, {"body": "PT MD Entertainment Tbk will issue 216,332,660 new shares, all of which will be taken up by PT Samuel International, increasing the company's total issued and paid-up capital to 9.72 billion shares and raising IDR 661.95 billion in additional capital. The new shares will be listed on October 28, 2024, following the issuance on October 25, 2024, and the announcement of the private placement results on October 29, 2024.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51216/film-investor-private-placement", "sub_sector": ["media-entertainment"], "tags": ["IDX", "IPO", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-10-22T10:20:38", "title": "PT MD Entertainment to issue 216 million new shares to PT Samuel International, raising IDR 661.95 billion in capital."}, {"body": "PT Mitra Investindo Tbk has established a new subsidiary, PT Karana Mitra Logistik (KML), with an authorized capital of IDR 10 billion and fully paid-up capital of IDR 22.5 billion, aiming to support the business activities of its subsidiary PT Pelayaran Karana Line. As of June 30, 2024, PT Mitra Investindo Tbk had cash and cash equivalents of IDR 157.40 billion, total assets of IDR 492.47 billion, and total equity of IDR 430.83 billion.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51215/mitra-investindo-establishes-subsidiary-idr-investment", "sub_sector": ["Logistics & Deliveries"], "tags": ["IDX", "Market Trends", "Financial Ratios", "Balance Sheets", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["MITI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-10-22T09:59:41", "title": "PT Mitra Investindo Tbk Establishes New Logistics Subsidiary with IDR 22.5 Billion Capital"}, {"body": "PT Wijaya Cahaya Timber Tbk, a plywood industrial producer, has secured a IDR 100 billion export working capital credit facility from Indonesia Eximbank with an interest rate of 5.31% and a 12-month maturity period. This financing facility is expected to reduce the company's loan costs due to the relatively lower interest rate charged by Indonesia Eximbank.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51214/fwct-secures-idr-financing-facilities-indonesia-eximbank", "sub_sector": ["Basic Materials"], "tags": ["Interest Rates", "IDX", "Timber", "Bonds", "Debt", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["FWCT.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-10-21T15:11:51", "title": "PT Wijaya Cahaya Timber receives IDR 100 billion export working capital credit from Indonesia Eximbank."}]